                            <comment id="13811161" author="anoop.hbase" created="Fri, 1 Nov 2013 10:36:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When we call modifyTable() with HTD including a new HCD, will this new HCD gets added to table?  I think no, as addColumn() should be used here. So this may be expected behaviour I would say Ram. Experts in this area , pls comment.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13811359" author="ram_krish" created="Fri, 1 Nov 2013 15:31:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually am not adding any new HCD only changing the existing attribute.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13811384" author="anoop.hbase" created="Fri, 1 Nov 2013 16:00:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes I mean to check whether any changes in HCDs in HTD will get affected by the modifyTable. If adding column is not considered then modifications to existing HCDs also not considered make sense IMO&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13812024" author="apurtell" created="Sat, 2 Nov 2013 15:18:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;At least the Javadoc could be clearer. Right now to change CF attributes one must use ModifyColumn, and to change table attributes one must use ModifyTable. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13812609" author="ram_krish" created="Mon, 4 Nov 2013 04:25:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Found that the modifyColumn or modifyTable works fine even if HCD is changed in modifyTable.  We have some internal code in that this does not seem to work.  Let me check on that and then see on what to do with this. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13812654" author="ram_krish" created="Mon, 4 Nov 2013 07:20:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Even modifyTable is also able to change the column descriptor.  Not an issue.  It was an issue with our internal code. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
